# Git — no remote push by default

## Push / delete-remote

- Do **not** run `git push`, `git push --delete`, `git push origin :branch`, force-push, or any command that creates/updates/deletes **remote** refs.
- **Exception:** user message **explicitly** orders a remote update, using unambiguous wording (examples: “push to origin”, “git push origin dev”, “delete remote branch X on origin”). Implied intent (“ship it”, “publish”, “sync”) is **not** enough.

## Local commits

- Local `git commit` only when the user explicitly asks to commit/checkpoint, or confirms a checkpoint per project policy.

## If user wants a branch on GitHub

- Stop after local branch/commit; tell them exactly what to run, **or** wait for explicit “push …”.
